Luxury in Leather-"Handmade in Germany since 1856"Available for sale is a new with tags soft brown leather ladies briefcase/handbag from Goldpfeil, a company located in Offenbach, Germany that has been producing some of the finest leathergoods in the world since 1856. This gorgeous bag is made with thick, buttery soft premium leather and its versatile design allows it to be used as an attaché style briefcase or a handbag. The hardware, silver in color and made with solid nickel includes five nickel feet on the bottom of the bag as well as a three digit nickel combination lock. On the front of the bag is a large pocket with ample space where your valuables can be secured by locking the bag. On the back of the bag is an additional hidden large compartment, secured by a magnetic snap closure. The interior is lined with a high quality slate colored fabric, imprinted throughout the bag with the Goldpfeil logo. There are two large zippered compartments framed with soft dark brown leather. As well there are two leather pen holders and a cell phone pocket. The top of the bag is designed with a wide 2.5" width with a zipper down the centre allowing for easy access to the bag. At the Goldpfeil shops in Germany, this bag sells for $579 Euro Dollars which is the equivalent of US $800 at todays exchange rates. Here are the dimensions:Length: 15.25" (39 cm.)Width: 4.5" (11.5 cm.) including the front pouchHeight: 11.5" (30 cm.) excluding the handlesStrap Drop: 5.25" (13.5 cm.)Goldpfeil's Oxford LeatherThe unique leather used for the Oxford Line is made exclusively for Goldpfeil. The selected skins from stable-fattened bulls from southern Germany-considered by many in the leather goods industry to be the best raw hides in the world are tanned for several months in the pit using natural vegetable substances and then aniline-dyed in the barrel. Their brilliant Oxford finish with its distinctive yet subtle two-tone effect is obtained in a manual process and further stresses the fascinating surface of this valuable leather. All of the models of the Oxford collection are tooled by hand and carefully sewn. For more than 155 years, the perfect craftsmanship of Goldpfeil's fine bag and briefcase makers has stood for an immaculate finish and extreme durability in of all their products. Supreme quality and understated elegance perfectly describes the image, style and quality that Goldpfeil has become famous for worldwide for over a century and a half. International bidders are welcome. We ship worldwide!
